---
import NotesLayout from '../../layouts/NotesLayout.astro';
---

<NotesLayout
  title="About this repository"
  description="What lives in this repo and how the site is built and deployed."
  tag="Repo"
  updated="28 Jun 2026"
>
  <p>
    This repo holds a small <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a> site for a
    tax / insurance / investment advisory practice, plus this private notes
    section. Everything ships as static HTML/CSS — zero client JS by default — so
    it's cheap to host and fast to load.
  </p>

  <h2>Layout</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><code>src/pages/</code> — one file per route. The marketing pages live at the top level; my notes live under <code>src/pages/notes/</code>.</li>
    <li><code>src/layouts/</code> — <code>Layout.astro</code> wraps the marketing pages; <code>NotesLayout.astro</code> wraps notes.</li>
    <li><code>src/components/</code> — shared <code>Header</code> / <code>Footer</code> for the marketing site (the notes section has its own).</li>
    <li><code>src/styles/global.css</code> — the design tokens (navy + gold) and shared classes, used by both sections.</li>
    <li><code>public/</code> — static assets copied as-is, plus <code>.nojekyll</code> so GitHub Pages serves Astro's <code>_astro/</code> folder.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Build &amp; deploy</h2>
  <p>
    GitHub Actions (<code>.github/workflows/deploy.yml</code>) builds on every push
    to <code>main</code> and publishes to GitHub Pages. The site is served under a
    project subpath, so <code>base</code> in <code>astro.config.mjs</code> is set to
    <code>/insurance</code> and every internal link is built from
    <code>import.meta.env.BASE_URL</code>.
  </p>
  <blockquote>
    Note to self: never hardcode <code>/insurance/...</code> in a link. Use the
    <code>link()</code> helper so the path survives a rename or a move to a custom domain.
  </blockquote>

  <h2>Local commands</h2>
  <pre><code>npm install
npm run dev      # http://localhost:4321
npm run build    # outputs ./dist
npm run preview</code></pre>

  <h2>Adding a note</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Create <code>src/pages/notes/&lt;slug&gt;.astro</code> using <code>NotesLayout</code> (copy an existing note).</li>
    <li>Add an entry to the <code>notes</code> array in <code>src/pages/notes/index.astro</code> so it shows on the list.</li>
    <li>Commit and push to <code>main</code> — the workflow deploys it.</li>
  </ol>
</NotesLayout>
